        "id": 1143760
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-22T01:04:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "There’s going to be some padding before this on 64-bit now, which we were trying to avoid.\n\nIt’s OK to put the new field where you did if we don’t care for this to have binary compatibility with existing deployed code yet, but you should arrange things so that they pad explicitly. That’s basically a requirement for proper cross-bitted operation with the process_types stuff.",
      "revId": "8fcd8ec184d4092b47654ed8c761e51e0f575d3f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "88656498_0b00c424",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_info.h",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 207,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-22T05:18:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done.\n\nI think it happened to work because the alignment for a uint64_t is the same as for an actual pointer on x64, so both this structure and the reader structure get implicitly padded in the same way (and similar for the x86 case when Traits::Pointer is a uint32t_t).\n\nBut better to be explicit.",
      "parentUuid": "2839d8b4_cd68e9f4",
      "revId": "8fcd8ec184d4092b47654ed8c761e51e0f575d3f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
